Camino Coffee Club went from a single farmers-market table to a DTC subscription
shipping up and down the West Coast. We asked founder "Theo" how the brand
behind the brand actually got built.

## The product sells the second bag, the content sells the first

"Nobody tastes your coffee through a screen," Theo says. "So the first bag is
sold entirely on story and craft - where the beans come from, who roasts them,
what the morning looks like." The content does the work the cup can't, until the
cup can.

## The unboxing is an ad

Camino treats the package as media. "Every box gets photographed by customers.
We designed it to be filmed. That's free top-of-funnel we don't pay for."

## What scaled it

A subscription built around habit, retention flows that bring lapsed members
back, and a content rhythm tied to the roast calendar. "Consumer brands on the
coast win on taste and story. We just made sure the story was always rolling."
